FINAL: Claude Shannon was born on April 30, 1916, and passed away on February 24, 2001. His three key contributions to information theory include: 1) Establishing the 'bit' as the fundamental unit of information linked to entropy; 2) Developing the mathematical model for communication systems and channel capacity; and 3) Establishing the connection between Boolean algebra and digital switching circuits.
